  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0d82\u0d9c\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0dba \u0db4\u0dbb\u0daf\u0dc0\u0db8\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0dc3\u0dd4\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2 4 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dda \u0dc0\u0da7\u0dba\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka beat Bangladesh to the Super 4 round",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lankan team managed to enter the Super 4 round of the Asia Cup cricket tournament. By winning the match against Bangladesh by 2 wickets.",
        "The Bangladesh team, who batted first in the match, managed to score 183 runs for 7 wickets in the scheduled 20 overs. The Sri Lankan team played the reply innings and managed to win the match by collecting 184 runs for the loss of 8 wickets in 19.2 overs.",
        "Kusal Mendis (60) and Pathum Nishanka (20) managed to give a successful start to the Sri Lankan team. The two put on 45 runs for the first wicket, after which Pathum, Charit, Dhanushka and Bhanuka were all out in 32 runs.",
        "However, captain Dasun Shanaka (45) along with Kusal took Sri Lanka's innings to 133 runs. Later, Kusal Mendis was dismissed for the fifth wicket at 131 runs, Vanindu Hasaranga was dismissed for the sixth wicket at 139 runs, Dasun Shanakat was also dismissed at 158 \u200b\u200bruns.",
        "At that time, Sri Lanka needed 26 runs to win in 2.1 overs. However, Chamika Karunaratne (16 (10 balls)) and Asitha Fernando (10 (3 balls)) brought Sri Lanka the match win."
      ],
